{
  "texts": [
    "The state-value function v π (s) seeks to estimate the expected total (discounted) reward value when the agent starts in state s and follows the policy π.",
    "Describing v π (s), one can note (see Eqs.",
    "[1] [2] [3] [4] the expected sum of future rewards for the states reached by adopting the policy π and performing the sequences of state transitions.",
    "(5), it is clear the dynamic nature of the computation of v π (s), and in Eq.",
    "(6) we have the discount value γ on the total expected reward."
  ]
}